Hypopygium (
Figs 16–17
). Laterosternite IX with 3 strong setae. Anal point drop-shaped (length 51 µm, width 17 µm) at the base with 3 strong medial and 5–6 weak lateral setae. Gonocoxite 102 µm long, with 3 setae on inner margin. Transverse sternapodeme 51 µm wide. Phallapodeme 75 µm long. Superior volsella elongated foot-shaped ( 58 µm long and 31 µm wide in the base) composed of dorsal and ventral lobes. Dorsal lobe bare with a fingershaped sclerotized projection ( 17 µm long), ventral lobe covered with microtrichia and bearing 1 strong apical seta ( 27 µm long) and 1 weaker seta ( 10–14 µm long) in the apical third. Inferior volsella with rounded apical part and covered with microtrichia. Gonostylus ( 136 µm long, 20–24 µm wide) narrowed in the proximal third and apically round. HR 0.75 .
